# Triverce Buyer Frontend — .cursorrules

## Scope

**This codebase is STRICTLY the Buyer-facing (B2C) Frontend for Triverce.**
It MUST NOT contain:
- Seller/Dashboard routes or pages
- Vendor registration flows
- Admin panel logic
- Any route prefixed with `/seller`, `/vendor`, `/admin`, or `/dashboard`

All seller-side and admin-side features live in separate repositories.

---

## Tech Stack

| Concern | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | React 19 |
| Bundler | Vite |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/vite` plugin) |
| Routing | React Router v7 |
| State Management | Zustand |
| HTTP Client | Axios |
| Language | TypeScript |

**No `tailwind.config.js` or `postcss.config.js` — Tailwind v4 is configured via `@theme` in `src/index.css`.**

---

## Business Model

- Triverce is a **Multi-vendor E-commerce Platform**.
- Every API response that includes product/order/cart data **MUST** carry `sellerId` and `sellerName`.
- **Cart and Order items are ALWAYS grouped by Seller.**
- Data models, interfaces, and TypeScript types must always reflect the multi-vendor nature.

---

## Design System

### Color Palette

| Token | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| Primary | `#002b5b` (blue-900) | Brand color, CTAs, key elements |
| Background | `bg-slate-50` | Page background |
| Surface | `#ffffff` | Cards, inputs, modals |
| Text Primary | `#0f172a` (slate-900) | Headings, primary text |
| Text Secondary | `#64748b` (slate-500) | Descriptions, metadata |
| Border | `#e2e8f0` (slate-200) | Dividers, input borders |
| Accent | `#1d4ed8` (blue-700) | Links, hover states |

### Inputs
- **Boxed inputs only** — all `<input>` elements must have rounded borders (Tailwind: `rounded-md` or `rounded-lg`).
- **NO underlined inputs** anywhere in the app.

### Typography
- Font: System font stack or a premium Google Font (e.g., Inter, DM Sans)
- Headings: bold, slate-900
- Body: slate-600, leading-relaxed

### Aesthetic
- Premium, clean, minimalist
- Generous whitespace
- Subtle shadows (`shadow-sm` / `shadow-md`)
- Rounded corners (`rounded-lg` for cards, `rounded-xl` for large containers)

---

## Architecture Principles

### SOLID — Applied Strictly

- **S**ingle Responsibility: each component/page does one thing. No God components.
- **O**pen/Closed: extend behavior via composition and props, not by modifying existing components.
- **L**iskov Substitution: all layout wrappers accept the same children contract.
- **I**nterface Segregation: custom hooks expose minimal, focused APIs.
- **D**ependency Inversion: services abstract Axios; stores abstract state; components are pure consumers.

### Separation of Concerns

```
UI Layer:     React Components / Pages
                ↓
Logic Layer:  Custom Hooks (useXxx) + Zustand Stores
                ↓
Data Layer:   API Services (Axios) + TypeScript Interfaces
```

**Rule: No business logic in components. No JSX in hooks/stores/services.**

### Component Rules
- One component per file.
- Named export preferred for components.
- Co-locate tests next to components (e.g., `ComponentName.test.tsx`).
- Prefer functional components with hooks only.

### Hook Rules
- One concern per hook.
- Named `use{Feature}{Action}` or `use{Context}{Feature}`.
- Return stable references; memoize objects/arrays when needed.

### Store Rules (Zustand)
- One store per domain (e.g., `useAuthStore`, `useCartStore`, `useProductStore`).
- Stores handle synchronous state and async actions.
- Keep stores thin — delegate API calls to services.

### Service Rules (Axios)
- One service per domain (e.g., `authService`, `productService`, `cartService`).
- Services create Axios instances with base URL and interceptors.
- No hardcoded URLs — use environment variables (`VITE_API_BASE_URL`).

### TypeScript Rules
- Strict mode is mandatory.
- All API response types must be defined in `src/types/`.
- Never use `any`. Use `unknown` with type narrowing when necessary.
- Multi-vendor fields (`sellerId`, `sellerName`) are REQUIRED on all product/order/cart types.

---

## File & Folder Structure

```
src/
├── components/          # Shared / reusable UI components
│   ├── ui/              # Primitive UI (Button, Input, Badge, Card, etc.)
│   └── layout/         # Layout-only components (Header, Footer, Sidebar)
├── pages/               # Route-level page components
├── layouts/             # Route layout wrappers (MainLayout, AuthLayout)
├── hooks/               # Custom hooks
├── store/               # Zustand stores
├── services/            # Axios API services
├── types/               # TypeScript interfaces & types
├── utils/               # Pure utility functions
└── assets/              # Static assets (images, fonts)
```

---

## Routing Convention

- Routes are defined in `src/App.tsx` using React Router v7.
- Use **nested routes** under `MainLayout` for all buyer-facing pages.
- Use `AuthLayout` for login and register pages.
- Route naming: kebab-case (e.g., `/order-confirmation`).

### Route Groups

| Layout | Prefix | Pages |
|---|---|---|
| `MainLayout` | `/` | Home, Shop, Product Detail, Cart, Checkout, Orders, Profile, etc. |
| `AuthLayout` | `/auth` | Login, Register |

---

## Environment Variables

```
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

---

## Code Style

- Use named exports.
- No default exports for stores or services.
- Prettier for formatting (if configured).
- ESLint for linting.
- Avoid inline styles — use Tailwind utility classes.
- Use `clsx` or `cn` utility for conditional classes.
